						<summary>

						<p>This is an incomplete inscription recording the consecration of god Vēdanāyaka-Perumāḷ and the endowment of some land for worship in the temple, by a chief named Aṅgarāyaṉ belonging to the Pullai Veṭṭuvar (?) community, who had the titles Naṟkāvēri-Nāḍāḻvāṉ, Dēśi Āḷappiṟandāṉ and Mummuḍiśoḻa-chakravartti.</p>						

						</summary>
